The paper focuses on author name disambiguation in the computer science bibliography DBLP, which is a digital library. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with digital libraries, information retrieval, and databases. Therefore, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.DB, and cs.SD are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses co-authorship networks to analyze the effectiveness of the method, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
